build/target-cache/
build/.fungi-cache/
**/.fungi-cache/
**/*.egraph.json
**/*.egraph.json.gz
.galerina/capabilities.local.json
.galerina/capabilities.local.*
packages-galerina/galerina-core/examples/benchmark-results/*.json
packages-galerina/galerina-devtools-benchmarks/results/history/
/notes/*
# ── Secrets / signing material — NEVER commit (CRITICAL, 2026-06-06) ──
.env.galerina-signing
.env.*.signing
**/*.signing
*.private.pem
**/*-private.pem
.env.local
.env.*.local
# Auto-provisioned dev signing pubkeys (zero-touch key lifecycle regenerates these per
# machine alongside the gitignored private key — they are build artifacts, not source).
**/governance/signing-key-*.pub.pem
# ── Build / test scratch (do not commit) ──
test-output.txt
**/*.pdb
build/*.out
# Ad-hoc audit scratch (tN.fungi fixtures at repo root) — no tracked tool generates it; local-only.
/_audit_tmp/
# Ad-hoc probe scratch — throwaway .mjs repros a session writes to exercise the compiler/runtime, then
# deletes. Named *.probe.mjs by convention so `git add -A` can never sweep one into a commit (a `cf-probe.mjs`
# slipped in once, 2026-06-26). No tracked tool emits these; always local-only.
**/*.probe.mjs
# NOTE: native benchmark binaries (**/*.exe under galerina-devtools-benchmarks/) are deliberately TRACKED
# (35 committed) so the cross-language benchmark compare runs without recompiling Rust — do NOT ignore *.exe.

# ── Ephemeral build/compile outputs (regenerated by `galerina build` + tests; never source) ──
build/*.wat
build/*.wasm
build/*.lmanifest
build/*.lmanifest.json
build/*.governance-impact.json
build/*.fungi
build/*.log
build/*.txt
build/_*.json
build/*.snap
# Runtime/test scratch (audit ledgers, egress/flight test dirs) — NOT build/graph or build/kb-graph
build/audit-log/
build/egress-it-*/
build/egress-test-*/
build/full-flight-*/
build/tower-logs/
build/receipt-ledger/
build/bench-report.md
build/*.dot

# build/graph: ignore the heavy REGENERATED artifacts (2.1 MB json churns every `graph` run;
# the json is rebuilt by `graph` — `graph query/explain/path` print "run graph first" if absent).
# KEEP the small human/AI nav docs (Galerina_GRAPH_REPORT.md, galerina-ai-map.md — AGENTS.md points to them).
build/graph/*.json
build/graph/*.html
build/kb-graph/*.json
build/kb-graph/*.dot
build/graph/*.dot

# Per-package .graph/ (the Hardened Border): same philosophy. package-graph.json is the HEAVY
# regenerated raw scan (node/edge dump, churns every `graph` run) and NOTHING reads the committed copy —
# the #149 border gate + CI RE-SCAN from source (zero-trust). KEEP the two curated files: boundary-policy.json
# (the allowlist the gate enforces — gitignoring it would fail-close the gate) and BOUNDARY.md (the small
# human-readable border report for PR-diff review). Do NOT use a blanket **/.graph/* — it would untrack
# boundary-policy.json and break the Hardened Border.
**/.graph/package-graph.json

# ── Nested-clone stopgap + sentinel scratch (RD-0124 hygiene; verified by adversarial audit ww6c274j4) ──
# galerina-devtools-project-graph is now committed IN-TREE like its siblings (the documented de-clone
# fix applied 2026-06-26: removed its nested .git/ + personal remote; absorbed into this monorepo).
# Sentinel-state test scratch: build/lss-test-<pid>-<n>/ from galerina-core-sentinel-state tests. The
# build/*.snap rule only matches snaps DIRECTLY under build/, so these nested-subdir snaps leaked into
# `git status`. Synthetic fixtures, no secrets.
build/lss-test-*/
# NOTE (do NOT ignore the per-package .graph/ files): boundary-policy.json (the hand-edited Hardened
# Border allowlist), BOUNDARY.md (observed-import surface + VIOLATIONS), and package-graph.json
# (externalDeps surface) are ALL governance border evidence and are TRACKED — an adversarial audit
# (ww6c274j4) proved that ignoring the two derived ones would silently hide border drift while CI
# `--check` is unwired (#149). Track them; revisit only once `--check` gates in CI.

# ── Transient cross-session handover briefs (worker→hub coordination, never production source) ──
# Workers drop HANDOVER-*.md at the repo ROOT to hand a finding to the hub session; they are consumed
# into commits/KB/memory and then ARCHIVED to ../Galerina-R-AND-D/_session-bridge/handovers-archive/.
# Ignore them at the root so a stray brief can't clutter the tree or be committed by accident.
/HANDOVER-*.md
